profile_positions.description:
During my internship I provided To-Increase with solid strategic advice where an Innovation Climate can thrive. The advice included corporate values ​​that are transformed into "enablers" for an innovation culture.
In addition to the advice, I was the main responsible person for the implementation of an Innovation Portal (ideas portal).

My main tasks were:
📍 Designing, setting up and implementing a process to analyze and verify new business opportunities, pitch new ideas and transfer them to the "Program Increment Planning" (this process is also known as the "Monkey Meeting");
📍 Set up a process to generate the most feasible ideas from our employees, customers and partners and lead them to an idea site;
📍 Design, program and implement a Shout-Out app to show appreciation for people who innovate (or contribute in any way to the company's core values);
📍 Designing and programming software (on a Raspberry Pi) to display various things on the TV screens throughout the office (customer success, innovation leaderboard (this is a shout-out app scoreboard), innovation dashboard (this is a "roadmap" for the ideas on the idea site));
📍 Set up An innovation tablet at the coffee machine to make voting through the Shout-Out app easy.
📍 Continuously advice the management on business operations, implementing ideas and adjusting course

I also contributed to automating various processes including:
📍 Fully automating and optimizing the Onboarding workflow for various business roles (manager and buddy of the new employee, Fleet manager, IT manager, Planning and People Operations).
📍 Fully automating the Innovation Decision Making Unit, whereby submitted ideas acquire ownership of the Product Owners and an automatic democratic voting process is set up to include feasible ideas in the Innovation Board Meetings with the entire Management.
